revision.text:
The '''Australasian Mechanical Copyright Owners Society''' ('''AMCOS''') is a [[copyright collective]] representing Australian and New Zealand [[Music publisher (popular music)|music publishers]] since 1979. The society's head offices are located in Sydney, Australia where its "line of business includes owning or leasing franchises, patents, and copyrights which they in turn license others to use."<ref name="Bloomberg">{{cite web | url = https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/companies/924477Z:AU-australasian-mechanical-copyright-owners-society-ltd | title = Australasian Mechanical Copyright Owners Society Ltd – Company Profile | publisher = [[Bloomberg L.P.]] | accessdate = 10 March 2017 }}</ref> It is a member of the [[Bureau International de l'Edition Mecanique]] (BIEM), the international mechanical rights coordinating organisation.<ref name="BIEM Member">{{cite web | url = http://www.biem.org/index.php?option=com_licensing&view=societes&Itemid=539&lang=en | title = Societies: AMCOS (Non-voting society) | publisher = [[Bureau International de l'Edition Mecanique]] (BIEM) | accessdate = 10 March 2017 }}</ref> AMCOS manages mechanical royalties, which is "the reproduction or copying and storage of music in different formats. This covers copying of songs and compositions by record labels or other parties to sell them on CD, DVD, online, for use as production music and for radio/TV programs."<ref name="AMCOS About">{{cite web | url = http://apraamcos.com.au/about-us/what-we-do/ | title = What We Do | publisher = [[Australasian Performing Right Association]] (APRA) &#124; Australasian Mechanical Copyright Owners Society (AMCOS) | accessdate = 10 March 2017 }}</ref>
Since 1997 the society has formed an alliance with [[Australasian Performing Right Association]] (APRA), which represents composers and lyricists, to provide "a one-stop service to music creators and music customers."<ref name="AMCOS About"/><ref>{{cite book|title=Encyclopedia of Australian Events 1997|year=1997|publisher=Macquarie Library}}</ref> Together they present the APRA Music Awards in [[APRA Awards (Australia)|Australia]] and [[APRA Awards (New Zealand)|New Zealand]] from 1998.
